title: TestGithubRelease fails on arm64

labels.name: bug
labels.description: A problem with current functionality, as opposed to missing functionality (enhancement)

labels.name: frozen-due-to-age
labels.description: Issues closed and untouched for a long time, together with being locked for discussion

body:
TestGithubRelease fails on arm64.

See the log:

```
=== RUN   TestGithubRelease
--- FAIL: TestGithubRelease (0.01s)
    upgrade_test.go:83: Error retrieving latest version couldn't find a release to download
    upgrade_test.go:86: Invalid upgrade release: v0.10.0-alpha -> v0.10.30, but got 
    upgrade_test.go:83: Error retrieving latest version couldn't find a release to download
    upgrade_test.go:86: Invalid upgrade release: v0.10.0-beta -> v0.10.30, but got 
    upgrade_test.go:83: Error retrieving latest version couldn't find a release to download
    upgrade_test.go:86: Invalid upgrade release: v0.11.0-beta0+40-g53cb66e-dirty -> v0.11.0-beta0, but got 
    upgrade_test.go:83: Error retrieving latest version couldn't find a release to download
    upgrade_test.go:86: Invalid upgrade release: v0.10.21 -> v0.10.30, but got 
    upgrade_test.go:83: Error retrieving latest version couldn't find a release to download
    upgrade_test.go:86: Invalid upgrade release: v0.10.29 -> v0.10.30, but got 
```

[Full log](https://buildd.debian.org/status/fetch.php?pkg=syncthing&arch=arm64&ver=0.13.9%2Bdfsg1-1&stamp=1467204073) is available in the Debian CI website.

See the status of Syncthing builds on other architectures [here](https://buildd.debian.org/status/package.php?p=syncthing).

Related Debian bug: [#828808](https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=828808)
